HEADWORD: Unbosom
<hw>Un*bos"om</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Unbosomed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Unbosoming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bosom</ets>.]</ety> <def>To disclose freely; to
reveal in confidence, as secrets; to confess; -- often used reflexively;
<as>as, to <ex>unbosom</ex> one's self</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

